                "href": "/profile/David-Moe-9"
            },
            "answer_text": "No, the US is not stealing oil from the Middle East, it is buying it, and it is paying the OPEC price to the oil producing countries in the Middle East. At this point in time, due the magic of hydraulic fracturing (\u201cfracking\u201d) the US is producing more of its own oil cheaper than it can buy it from OPEC, so American oil production is reaching an all-time high. It can also buy oil from Canada at a discount to OPEC prices, since Canadian production of heavy oil from its oil sands (\u201ctar sands\u201d) is also rising and Canadian oil companies are willing to undercut OPEC prices to make sales. Canadian oil is backing Middle Eastern oil out of the US market and Canada now accounts for over 1/3 of America\u2019s falling oil imports, more than all the Middle Eastern countries combined. Between American \u201cfracking\u201d and Canadian \u201ctar sands\u201d, North America is approaching continental oil self-sufficiency. This is causing a lot of problems for Middle Eastern oil producing countries because they no longer have the US over a barrel for oil supply. Both the price and the US demand for their oil is falling, and they really need the US money to finance the lavish spending style their ruling classes have gotten used to. ",
