            "answer_text": "American companies negotiated with rulers in the Middle East to find, obtain and produce oil.   Some of these companies have been purchased back by the nations that they originally worked with.  For example,  Saudi Aramco was originally part of Standard of California Oil, which became Standard Oil, which was purchased by Exxon.  The Saudi government bought back the original piece by about 1980 and moved the head offices back in 1988. Every barrel of oil was paid for.  Sometimes, the negotiated rates were better than the world price but that is negotiation, not stealing. The US government is not in the oil business. ",
